[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 585 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Thu 9 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-07/10/c_81043.htm


On 9 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 10 Jul 2020):
- 4 new cases of confirmed infections (all, imported cases, 1 in Liaoning province, 1 in Shanghai municipality, 1 in Shanxi province, and 1 in Inner Mongolia autonomous region), 3 new cases of suspected infections (all imported into Shanghai municipality), and no deaths.
- A total of 1962 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 585 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 609 recovered and discharged from hospital; 765 615 close contacts with infected patients; and 3796 are under medical observation.
- 3 new asymptomatic cases (all imported cases); no asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 113 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 82 imported cases).
- 1365 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 42 cases since 8 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The 4 new confirmed cases in the last 24 hours were all imported and no cases were reported from Beijing.

There were 3 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, there have been 37 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infections reported by China.

Hong Kong reported 42 new cases. At the time of preparation of this report, the Centre for Health Protection in Hong Kong had not issued a press release on these cases. A media reported dated 9 Jul 2020 mentioned there was an increase in local cases (42) with 8 having a recent travel history. Most of the local cases were linked to clusters from restaurants, taxi drivers, and elderly care centres. Effective Saturday (11 Jul 2020), restaurants have to limit maximum capacity to 60%, and tables no more than 8 individuals, bars had to limit tables to 4, and Gyms, party rooms and karaoke bars limit to 8 at tables (https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3092459/coronavirus-least-15-more-covid-19-cases-detected).

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2, many of whom are detected as asymptomatic at the time of positive PCR testing. Hong Kong is dealing with increased transmission associated with lifting of restrictions.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7560034,155. - Mod.MPP]

