[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:
- The Americas region reported 59.1% of the global newly reported cases and 67.8% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period, maintaining its dominance of the most severely affected region. The USA reported 41.5% of the newly confirmed cases in the region (50 263), and Brazil reported 37.4% (45 305), Mexico 5.2% (6258), Colombia 3.5% (4213), Peru 3.0% (3575), Argentina 2.5% (2979), and Chile 1.7% (2064).
- The European region reported 9.8% of the global newly reported cases and 10.7% of the newly confirmed deaths in the region. Russia reported 32.4% (6509) of the regional newly confirmed cases, followed by Kazakhstan 9.8% (1962), Israel 7.0% (1406), Turkey 5.2% (1041), Ukraine 4.0% (810), the UK 3.1% (630), Romania 2.8% (555), Azerbaijan 2.7% (542), Armenia 2.6% (526), and Sweden 2.6 (514).
- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.5% of the global newly reported cases and 8.3% of global newly reported fatalities. Pakistan reported 19.3% (3359) of the regional newly reported cases followed by Saudi Arabia 17.5%, (3036), Iraq 15.8% (2741), Iran 15.5% (2691), Oman 7.0% (1210), Egypt 5.9% (1025), Kuwait 4.4% (762), and Bahrain (610) and Qatar (608) at 3.5 % each.
- The African region reported 6.2% of the global newly reported cases and 2.6% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 68.8% (8810) of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Ghana 6.7% (854), Cote d'Ivoire 4.2% (538), Algeria 3.7% (469), and Nigeria 3.6% (460).
- The Western Pacific region reported 1.5% of the global newly reported cases and 0.14% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 81.1% (2486) of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Japan 6.4% (197), Singapore 5.2% (158), Australia 4.3% (131), South Korea 1.6% (49), and China 1.1% (33).
- The South East Asia region reported 14.9% of the global newly reported cases and 10.5% of global deaths. India reported 81.5% (24 879) of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 11.4% (3489), Indonesia 6.1% (1853), and Nepal 0.84% (255).

Impression (unchanged): The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis, followed by the South East Asia region, then Europe and the Eastern Mediterranean alternating on a daily basis of their order, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific representing the lowest daily caseload of all of the regions.

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 9 Jul 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. - Mod.MPP]

